Proposal Forge — Handoff Document
Date: 2026-06-25 Status: Core engine operational. Proposal generation live with Claude Sonnet 4. Learning loop architecture implemented. Outcome tracking API ready. Frontend needs outcome buttons.
________________________________________
What Works
1. Proposal Generation (app/api/generate/route.ts)
•	Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 (Claude Sonnet 4)
•	System prompt: Dynamically assembled from forge_rules table in Supabase
•	Fallback doctrine: Hardcoded if DB read fails — generation never breaks
•	Rate limit: 1 free proposal/month, tracked via profiles.proposals_this_month
•	Database insert: Stores user_id, client_name, project_type, content, platform, score_avg
2. Learning Loop (app/api/learn/route.ts)
•	Trigger: POST to /api/learn (manual button or every 5 proposals)
•	Minimum data: 3 proposals with non-pending outcomes
•	Process: Reads last 20 proposals → sends to Claude with analysis prompt → extracts one new rule → writes to forge_rules with source = 'learned'
•	Result: Next proposal generation automatically uses the new rule
3. Outcome Logging (app/api/outcome/route.ts)
•	Endpoint: POST /api/outcome
•	Body: { proposal_id, outcome } where outcome is hired | no_response | rejected
•	Security: Verifies proposal belongs to requesting user before updating
•	Status: API ready. Frontend buttons not yet implemented.
